  (text "DISPLAY CHAIN NOTES:\\nLT8618SX (QFN-56): MIPI DSI → HDMI 2.0. I2C address 0x75.\\n  TMDS AC coupling: 100nF 50V X7R on all 8 TMDS signals (C_H5-H8)\\n  HPD: 1kΩ pullup to +5V (HDMI spec requires 5V hot-plug detect)\\n  DDC SCL/SDA: 1kΩ pullups to +3V3 (EDID I2C at 100kHz)\\nCBTL04GP054 (XSON-16): 4-lane MIPI switch\\n  SEL=LOW  → Path A → LT8618SX → micro-HDMI Type D\\n  SEL=HIGH → Path B → J_DSI FPC → RPi5 DSI display\\n  SEL controlled by QRB2210 GPIO via TXS0108E level shifter\\nJ_HDMI: Molex 47151-2001 micro-HDMI Type D (19-pin)\\n  RPi5 compatible: standard micro-HDMI to HDMI Type A cable works\\nJ_DSI: Molex 503480-2200 22-pin 0.5mm FPC (RPi5 DSI display cable)\\nNOTE: LT8618SX and CBTL04GP054 symbols require custom library entry\\n  Add via KiCad Symbol Editor using pinouts in DESIGN_SPEC.md"
    (at 20 145 0)
    (effects (font (size 1.27 1.27)) (justify left top))
    (uuid "c1d780f0-50de-446c-8be8-4545d7b11024")
  )
